<br>
Melody of Ervaj (lvl 50, 5% haste) stacks with other bard/chanter/shaman haste but will not exceed cap, and Composition of Ervaj (lvl 60, 10% haste) stacks with other bard/chanter/shaman haste but will not exceed cap. Neither exceeds the haste cap. There was much gnashing of teeth amongst the high end bards that these songs were &quot;worthless&quot; because most of the melees they grouped with hit the haste cap via their dragon haste + chanter haste.<br>
<br>
Battle Cry of the Vah Shir (lvl 52, 15%) stacks with chanter/bard/shaman haste and allows you to exceed cap, and War Cry of the Vah Shir (lvl 60, 25%) stacks with chanter/bard/shaman haste, and allows you to exceed cap. The Vah Shir songs were, until recently, bugged in the following way --- as far as I know this is still the case:<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<br>
&quot;If you don't have any other haste (item or spell/song will fix it), then Battlecry alone will set your speed to 15% of normal (rather than 115% of normal)...If all of the melees in your group have haste items, or shaman or enchanter haste, or you sing another haste song, then Battlecry will work properly and improve the haste.&quot; -from post on the bard board. <br>
